frameDefinitions: An Agent or Cause makes a Patient sharper or duller.
An Agent cuts a Item into Pieces using an Instrument (which may or may not be expressed).
In this frame a Grinder or Grinding_cause causes a Patient to be broken into smaller pieces.
An Agent alters some Material in some useful way by means of some chemical or physical Alterant.
The Invader enters a Land in an aggressive attempt to cripple or dominate its people and its government.
The words in this frame describe the manipulation of an Entity by an Agent.
frameExamples: John is in the basement <t>sharpening</t> his axe.
At the ceremony, the CEO <t>cut</t> the red ribbon hanging across the main entrance into a glorious confetti.
Bill <t>ground</t> the coffee beans into a fine powder.
Native Americans <t>dyed</t> textiles with dyes made from cedar strips.
In August 1990 ,Iraq was <t>invading</t> Kuwait , which led to the Gulf war .
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Agent</fen> causes the <fen>Patient</fen> to become more or less sharp.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity that is sharpened.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that produces the state of sharpness.  Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic of <fen>Cause</fen>s.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> sharpens <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Agent</fen> sharpens the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is the person cutting the <fen>Item</fen> into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The item which is being cut into <fen>Pieces</fen>.
The <fen>Pieces</fen> are the parts of the original <fen>Item</fen> which are the result of the slicing.
When the slicing occurs.
Where the slicing takes place.
An animate or inanimate entity, a force, or event that grinds. Volitionality is not a necessary characteristic.
The <fen>Grinder</fen> breaks the <fen>Patient</fen> into smaller pieces.
The <fen>Patient</fen> is the entity which undergoes the change brought about by the <fen>Grinder</fen> or <fen>Grinding_cause</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when  the <fen>Grinder</fen> grinds the <fen>Patient</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where  the <fen>Grinder</fen> grinds the <fen>Patient</fen>.
The <fen>Agent</fen> is a person who applies the Process to the Material.
The <fen>Alterant</fen> causes a change in the <fen>Material</fen>.
The <fen>Material</fen> is altered by the <fen>Agent</fen> in some useful way.
The point in time or period during which the treatment of the <fen>Material</fen> takes place.
The location in which the <fen>Material</fen>s are processed, often a purpose-built facility such as a tannery or water treatment plant.
The political area that is being crippled by the <fen>Invader</fen>'s entry.
The army or other self-directed entity that is entering the <fen>Land</fen> in a hostile manner.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Invader</fen> invades <fen>Land</fen>.
This role identifies the location where the <fen>Invader</fen> invades the <fen>Land</fen>.

The <fen>Agent</fen> manipulates an object. <fen>Agent</fen> typically refers to animate beings, but is also extended to mechanical and other inanimate objects.  <fen>Agent</fen> is most frequently expressed as the external argument of verbs:
The <fen>Entity</fen> being manipulated often occurs as the direct object of verbs:

The part of the <fen>Agent</fen>'s body being used to manipulate the <fen>Entity</fen> may also be expressed. While the default is for an <fen>Agent</fen> to use his/her hands, other body parts may be specified. This frame element usually occurs as a PP-complement.
When the manipulation takes place
The spatial setting in which the manipulation takes place.
listRoleExamples: <fex>The smith</fex> sharpened many knives in the days before the war.
Several cuts into the log had dulled <fex>the blade</fex>.
<fex>The relentless impacts against the wood</fex> gradually blunted the edge of this axe.
People back then had to chop <fex>firewood</fex> all day long.
<fex>The wind</fex> ground the leaves into a fine powder.
Stu treated <fex>the lumber</fex> with magical waterproofing fairydust.
Henry II had made no attempt to invade <fex>France.</fex>
Indeed , three months later <fex>Hitler</fex> invaded Austria.
<fex>A robot arm</fex> grasps the box on the conveyor belt and seals it.
Squeeze <fex>the ball</fex> as many times as you can.
Kim grasped the needle <fex>between finger and thumb</fex>.
I seized the letter <fex>before he did</fex>.
<fex>In the hallway</fex> he managed to grabthe monarch by the ankles
